Given the function $f(x) = \frac{x^2}{1+x^2}$.

$(1)$ Calculate the values of $f(2) + f\left(\frac{1}{2}\right)$, $f(3) + f\left(\frac{1}{3}\right)$, $f(4) + f\left(\frac{1}{4}\right)$, and infer a general conclusion (proof not required);

